org.safs.logging

Class MessageTypeInfo

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.safs.logging.MessageTypeInfo

  • public class MessageTypeInfo
extends java.lang.Object
    This helper class encapsulates all constant information related to a particular message type, including the STAF level that the type maps to, the prefix used in the text log, and the type string used in the xml log.

    To get all constant information associated with a message type in a MessageTypeInfo, use the static get method:

    MessageTypeInfo info = MessageTypeInfo.get(msgType);

    • Method Detail

      • get

        public static MessageTypeInfo get(int type)
        Returns a MessageTypeInfo for a message type.

        Parameters:
        type - the message type.
        Returns:
        the MessageTypeInfo for the specified type; null if type is not a standard SAFS message type.

      • typeBelongsToLevel

        public static boolean typeBelongsToLevel(int type,
                         int level)
        Tests if a message type "belongs to" a log level.

        A message will not be written to a log if its type does not pass the test against the log level of that log.

        Parameters:
        type - the message type to test.
        level - the log level to test against. One of the LOGLEVEL constants defined by AbstractLogFacility.
        Returns:
        true if type passes the test of level; false if not.
